text = "Tutorial Second Mission:


In this mission, your leadership skills are put to the test. You need to delegate tasks to our team members to keep the excavation running smoothly. Here’s how it works:

Mission:
Assign the six tasks to our six team members. Each member is either good or bad at each task, so choose wisely to ensure our excavation progresses efficiently.

How to Assign Tasks:


Drag and Drop: Click on a task and drag them onto a team member you want them to perform.

Right Click for Info: If you need more information about a task, right-click on them. 

For More information about a team member you can just hover over them.

Tasks to be Assigned:

Shoveling & Digging
Cleaning
Drawing
Organization & Documentation
Photography & Surveying
Documentation & Finding Communication


Tips for Success:

Know Your Team: Hover over a team member to understand their strengths and weaknesses. This will help you assign them to the tasks where they will perform best.

Balance the Work: Make sure each task is matched with the team member best suited for it. This will maximize efficiency and ensure a smooth operation.

Remember, the success of our excavation depends on your ability to delegate effectively. Get to know your team, make informed decisions, and let’s keep unearthing the secrets of Heuneburg!

Let’s get to work and make today another day of great discoveries!"

